properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Rain associated with a strong low pressure trough over eastern Hudson Bay will affect Kimmirut and Iqaluit today. As the trough passes by tonight, the rain will taper off. properties.Title: Tropical Cyclone Information Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: For Hurricane Humberto. The next information statement will be issued by 09:00 p.m. ADT. Humberto will continue to approach Canadian marine waters this evening. It will begin to affect the Scotian Slope and the southern Grand Banks later tonight and Friday. 1. Summary of basic information at 03:00 p.m. ADT. Location: Near 37.8 North 59.7 West. About 680 kilometres south of Sable Island. Maximum sustained winds: 176 kilometres per hour. Present movement: Northeast at 33 kilometres per hour. Minimum central pressure: 958 millibars. 2. Public weather impacts and warnings summary. No significant effects are expected over land. a. Wind. No significant wind expected. b. Rainfall. No significant rain expected. c. Surge/Waves. Swells of 2 to 3 metres will reach the Atlantic coast of Nova Scotia Friday morning, and 3 to 5 metres swells will then reach southern Newfoundland Friday night and early Saturday. Waves will break higher along some of the coastlines, and dangerous rip currents are possible. 3. Marine weather impacts and warnings summary. Storm warnings are in effect for East Scotian Slope - eastern half, Laurentian Fan, and Southwestern Grand Banks. Gales warnings are in effect for Georges Bank, West Scotian Slope, Sable - eastern half, East Scotian Slope - western half, and Banquereau - southern half. Gale to Storm Force winds are forecast over the Scotian Slope waters, Laurentian Fan, Banquereau, and the southern Grand Banks Friday into Saturday. As the winds increase, large waves of 7 to 10 metres will build over offshore waters Friday and Friday night. Some of these waves could exceed 10 metres southeast of the track as the centre passes over Laurentian Fan and the southern Grand Banks. Forecaster(s): Clements/Couturier. ### Please continue to monitor alerts issued by the Canadian Hurricane Centre and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.

properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Strong winds that may cause damage are expected or occurring. Strong westerly winds with gusts up to 100 km/h will develop late this evening in the Canada Bay area. These winds are expected to diminish below warning criteria by early Friday morning. ### Damage to buildings, such as to roof shingles and windows, may occur. High winds may toss loose objects or cause tree branches to break. Wind warnings are issued when there is a significant risk of damaging winds. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.
